modules.description: This module implements zlib compression and decompression for strings, handling errors such as truncation and compression failures. It provides direct access to compression with adjustable levels and header inclusion, and safe decompression with size limits. Use cases include reducing memory footprint for data transmission or storage, and parsing zlib-compressed network payloads with safety checks.

This module provides gzip compression and decompression for strings with support for size and checksum validation, ensuring safe and controlled handling of compressed data in memory. It allows precise configuration of compression levels and decompression constraints, making it suitable for protocols requiring embedded compression or integrity checks. The zlib submodule extends this functionality with direct access to zlib-format compression, header control, and error handling for truncated or malformed input. Together, they enable tasks like compressing data for network transmission, validating compressed payloads, and safely decompressing untrusted or incomplete inputs.
